Class CompositeHL7v2Exception

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Throwable
      • java.lang.Exception
        • java.lang.RuntimeException
          • org.openehealth.ipf.modules.hl7.AbstractHL7v2Exception
            • org.openehealth.ipf.modules.hl7.CompositeHL7v2Exception
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Iterable<AbstractHL7v2Exception>
    Deprecated. 
    Validation in HAPI 2.2 does not require composite exceptions

    public class CompositeHL7v2Exception
extends AbstractHL7v2Exception
implements Iterable<AbstractHL7v2Exception>
    This exception is used to wrap one of more HL7v2Exceptions, e.g. as result for validating a message that has errors in multiple places. It contains an own error message, which populateMessage(Message, AckTypeCode) writes into MSA-3.
    Author:
    Christian Ohr, Marek Vaclavik
